<TITLE> Ayub to skipper NCA in Academy Cup series </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, April 26 (bdnews24.com) - Middle-order batsman Marshal Ayub has been named captain of the National Cricket Academy in the third Grameenphone-BCB Academy Cup series against Sri Lanka U-19 team. The announcement came on Sunday at a press conference during the unveiling ceremony of the tournament's logo at the Sher-e-Bangla National Stadium. The competition, which starts on May 4, includes two four-day matches and five one-day matches to be played in Chittagong, Sylhet and Dhaka. Opener Jahurul Islam will be Ayub's deputy in the four-day matches, said chief selector Rafiqul Alam. Alam also named of 12 new players, who have been enrolled for the April-July session of the GP-BCB Academy. Rubaba Dowla, chief communications officer of GP, Nizamuddin Ahmed Chowdhury, the acting CEO of the BCB and Khaled Mahmud, the team operations manager of the Academy also spoke on the occasion. GP-BCB National Cricket Academy squad: Marshal Ayub (captain), Jahurul Islam (vice-captain), Nasiruddin Faruque, Imtiaz Hossain, Arman Hossain, Farhad Hossain, Shuvagoto Hom, Raihan Arafat, Saqlain Sajib, Robiul Islam, Shafiul Islam, Arafat Slahuddin, Muktar Ali, Kamrul Islam and Safaq Al Jabir. bnd
